s and presents it systematically in chronological order.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aAlte Geschichte. 4aIsaurien. 4aRömisches Reich. 4aZeno ‹Imperium Byzantinum, Imperator› (440-491 n. Chr.). 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aAncient history.  aIsauria.  aRoman Empire.  aZeno (emperor).08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2005z9783110277111oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2005z9783110276985oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311018899840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110927405zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110927405zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110927405/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2005  aZDB-23-DGGb2005  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014  aZDB-23-GOA